@startuml RiderMatchingService_Annotated

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam nodesep 35
skinparam ranksep 30
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

skinparam class {
    BackgroundColor #2ECC71
    BorderColor #1A1A1A
    FontColor White
    FontSize 10
}

skinparam enum {
    BackgroundColor #2ECC71
    BorderColor #1A1A1A
    FontColor White
    FontSize 10
}

skinparam interface {
    BackgroundColor #2ECC71
    BorderColor #1A1A1A
    FontColor White
    FontSize 10
}

title <size:18>Quick Commerce Rider Matching Service - Class Diagram (Annotated for Interview)</size>\n<size:11>Trace: "Order placed at dark store. System finds nearest available rider, assigns, rider picks up, delivers in 10 min."</size>


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 1: FACADE
' ====================================================================
class RiderMatchingService <<Facade>> {
    - riderPool : RiderPool
    - matchingStrategy : MatchingStrategy
    - assignmentPolicy : AssignmentPolicy
    - notificationService : NotificationService
    - loadBalancer : LoadBalancer
    --
    + findRider(deliveryRequest) : MatchResult
    + reassignRider(deliveryId) : MatchResult
    + setMatchingStrategy(strategy) : void
    + setAssignmentPolicy(policy) : void
    + getRiderAvailability(zone) : int
}

note top of RiderMatchingService #BBDEFB
    **STEP 1 - Start here.**
    "Order is packed at a dark store.
    System needs a rider NOW (10 min SLA).
    RiderMatchingService is the **Facade**
    — coordinates matching strategy,
    assignment policy, rider pool, and
    notifications. Returns a MatchResult."
    **Pattern: Facade | SRP, DIP**
end note


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 2: DELIVERY REQUEST + ORDER
' ====================================================================
class DeliveryRequest {
    - requestId : String
    - order : Order
    - pickupLocation : Location
    - dropoffLocation : Location
    - requestedAt : LocalDateTime
    - priority : DeliveryPriority
    - maxWaitTimeSeconds : int
    - requiredVehicle : VehicleType
    --
    + getDistance() : double
    + isExpired() : boolean
    + getElapsedSeconds() : long
}

class Order {
    - orderId : String
    - customerId : String
    - items : List<OrderItem>
    - totalWeight : double
    - isFragile : boolean
    - orderValue : double
    --
    + requiresSpecialHandling() : boolean
    + getWeight() : double
}

class OrderItem {
    - name : String
    - quantity : int
    - weight : double
}

class Location {
    - latitude : double
    - longitude : double
    - address : String
    - zone : ServiceZone
    --
    + distanceTo(other) : double
    + isWithinRadius(center, radiusKm) : boolean
}

enum DeliveryPriority {
    EXPRESS
    STANDARD
    SCHEDULED
}

enum ServiceZone {
    ZONE_A
    ZONE_B
    ZONE_C
    ZONE_D
}

note top of DeliveryRequest #C8E6C9
    **STEP 2 - What needs delivering?**
    "**DeliveryRequest** wraps an Order with
    pickup (dark store) and dropoff (customer)
    locations. Has priority (EXPRESS for
    10-min delivery), max wait time, and
    required vehicle type."
    "**Location** has lat/lng, zone, and
    distanceTo() for proximity checks."
end note

DeliveryRequest --> Order : for order >
DeliveryRequest --> Location : pickup/dropoff >
DeliveryRequest --> DeliveryPriority
Order *-- OrderItem
Location --> ServiceZone


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 3: RIDER MODEL
' ====================================================================
class Rider {
    - riderId : String
    - name : String
    - phone : String
    - currentLocation : Location
    - status : RiderStatus
    - vehicle : VehicleType
    - rating : double
    - activeDeliveryCount : int
    - maxConcurrentDeliveries : int
    - currentZone : ServiceZone
    - lastAssignedAt : LocalDateTime
    - totalDeliveriesToday : int
    --
    + isAvailable() : boolean
    + canTakeMore() : boolean
    + distanceTo(location) : double
    + assign() : void
    + release() : void
    + updateLocation(loc) : void
}

enum RiderStatus {
    AVAILABLE
    ON_DELIVERY
    ON_BREAK
    OFFLINE
    RETURNING_TO_ZONE
}

enum VehicleType {
    BICYCLE
    SCOOTER
    MOTORCYCLE
    CAR
}

class RiderPool {
    - riders : Map<String, Rider>
    - zoneIndex : Map<ServiceZone, List<Rider>>
    --
    + getAvailableRiders(zone) : List<Rider>
    + getAvailableRiders(zone, vehicleType) : List<Rider>
    + getRider(riderId) : Rider
    + registerRider(rider) : void
    + updateRiderLocation(riderId, location) : void
    + getRiderCountByZone() : Map<ServiceZone, Integer>
}

note top of Rider #C8E6C9
    **STEP 3 - Who delivers?**
    "**Rider** has location, status, vehicle type,
    rating, and concurrent delivery count.
    isAvailable() = AVAILABLE + canTakeMore().
    **RiderPool** indexes riders by zone for
    fast lookup. Quick commerce needs
    sub-second matching — zone indexing
    avoids scanning all riders."
end note

Rider --> RiderStatus
Rider --> VehicleType
Rider --> Location : current >
Rider --> ServiceZone : operates in >
RiderPool o--> Rider : manages >
RiderMatchingService --> RiderPool


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 4: MATCHING STRATEGY — Strategy Pattern (CORE)
' ====================================================================
interface MatchingStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + findCandidates(request, riders) : List<RiderCandidate>
}

class NearestRiderStrategy {
    - maxRadiusKm : double
    --
    + findCandidates(request, riders) : List<RiderCandidate>
}

class RatingBasedStrategy {
    - minRating : double
    --
    + findCandidates(request, riders) : List<RiderCandidate>
}

class LeastLoadedStrategy {
    --
    + findCandidates(request, riders) : List<RiderCandidate>
}

class CompositeMatchingStrategy {
    - strategies : List<MatchingStrategy>
    --
    + findCandidates(request, riders) : List<RiderCandidate>
}

class RiderCandidate {
    - rider : Rider
    - distanceToPickup : double
    - estimatedPickupTimeMin : double
    - score : double
    --
    + getScore() : double
}

note bottom of MatchingStrategy #FFE0B2
    **STEP 4 - How to find the right rider? (KEY STEP)**
    "Multiple riders are online. Which one?
    **Strategy Pattern** — matching logic is pluggable."

    "**NearestRider**: closest to dark store.
    **RatingBased**: highest rated first.
    **LeastLoaded**: fewest active deliveries."

    "**CompositeStrategy** chains them:
    filter by distance, rank by (rating + load).
    Each returns scored RiderCandidates."

    "Quick commerce peak: switch to NearestRider
    for speed. Off-peak: use BestFit for quality."
    **Pattern: Strategy + Composite | OCP, DIP**
end note

MatchingStrategy <|.. NearestRiderStrategy
MatchingStrategy <|.. RatingBasedStrategy
MatchingStrategy <|.. LeastLoadedStrategy
MatchingStrategy <|.. CompositeMatchingStrategy
CompositeMatchingStrategy o--> MatchingStrategy : chains >
MatchingStrategy --> RiderCandidate : returns >
RiderCandidate --> Rider
RiderMatchingService --> MatchingStrategy : delegates >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 5: SCORING — Weighted Scorer
' ====================================================================
class RiderScorer {
    - weights : Map<ScoringFactor, Double>
    --
    + score(rider, request) : double
    + setWeight(factor, weight) : void
}

enum ScoringFactor {
    DISTANCE
    RATING
    CURRENT_LOAD
    DELIVERY_COUNT_TODAY
    VEHICLE_FIT
    ZONE_FAMILIARITY
}

note bottom of RiderScorer #FFE0B2
    **STEP 5 - Score and rank candidates.**
    "Each rider gets a composite score:
    Score = w1*distance + w2*rating
    + w3*load + w4*vehicleFit"

    "Weights are tunable per zone/time.
    Peak hours: weight distance heavily.
    Off-peak: weight rating more."
    "Separating scoring from matching
    keeps both extensible." **(SRP)**
end note

RiderScorer --> ScoringFactor
RiderMatchingService --> RiderScorer : ranks with >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 6: ASSIGNMENT POLICY — Strategy Pattern
' ====================================================================
interface AssignmentPolicy <<Strategy>> {
    + assign(candidates, request) : AssignmentResult
}

class DirectAssignPolicy {
    --
    + assign(candidates, request) : AssignmentResult
}

class BroadcastAssignPolicy {
    - timeoutSeconds : int
    --
    + assign(candidates, request) : AssignmentResult
}

class BatchAssignPolicy {
    - batchWindowMs : int
    --
    + assign(candidates, request) : AssignmentResult
}

class AssignmentResult {
    - assignedRider : Rider
    - estimatedPickupMin : double
    - estimatedDeliveryMin : double
    - fallbackTriggered : boolean
}

note bottom of AssignmentPolicy #FFCDD2
    **STEP 6 - How to assign?**
    "Found candidates. Now how to assign?"

    "**DirectAssign**: auto-assign top candidate.
    (Fast. Used in quick commerce peak.)
    **BroadcastAssign**: push to top N riders,
    first to accept wins. (Used for Scheduled.)
    **BatchAssign**: collect requests for X ms,
    then optimally pair riders and orders.
    (Used for multi-order optimization.)"
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP, DIP**
end note

AssignmentPolicy <|.. DirectAssignPolicy
AssignmentPolicy <|.. BroadcastAssignPolicy
AssignmentPolicy <|.. BatchAssignPolicy
AssignmentPolicy --> AssignmentResult : returns >
RiderMatchingService --> AssignmentPolicy : delegates >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 7: LOAD BALANCER — Prevents Overload
' ====================================================================
class LoadBalancer {
    - zoneCapacity : Map<ServiceZone, Integer>
    - surgeThreshold : double
    --
    + isZoneOverloaded(zone) : boolean
    + getSurgeMultiplier(zone) : double
    + canAcceptRequest(zone) : boolean
    + rebalanceRiders() : List<RebalanceCommand>
}

class RebalanceCommand {
    - riderId : String
    - fromZone : ServiceZone
    - toZone : ServiceZone
    - reason : String
}

note bottom of LoadBalancer #D1C4E9
    **STEP 7 - Zone capacity management.**
    "Zone A has 50 orders but only 10 riders.
    LoadBalancer detects overload and:
    1. Triggers surge multiplier (incentives).
    2. Issues RebalanceCommands to move
       idle riders from Zone C to Zone A.
    3. Rejects new requests if capacity
       is fully exhausted."
end note

LoadBalancer --> ServiceZone
LoadBalancer --> RebalanceCommand : issues >
RiderMatchingService --> LoadBalancer


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 8: DELIVERY STATE — State Pattern
' ====================================================================
interface DeliveryState <<State>> {
    + assignRider(delivery, rider) : void
    + pickUp(delivery) : void
    + deliver(delivery) : void
    + cancel(delivery, reason) : void
    + fail(delivery, reason) : void
}

class PendingState {
    + assignRider(delivery, rider) : void
    + cancel(delivery, reason) : void
}

class AssignedState {
    + pickUp(delivery) : void
    + cancel(delivery, reason) : void
    + fail(delivery, reason) : void
}

class PickedUpState {
    + deliver(delivery) : void
    + fail(delivery, reason) : void
}

class DeliveredState {
    ' terminal
}

class CancelledState {
    ' terminal
}

class FailedState {
    + assignRider(delivery, rider) : void
}

class Delivery {
    - deliveryId : String
    - request : DeliveryRequest
    - rider : Rider
    - currentState : DeliveryState
    - status : DeliveryStatus
    - assignedAt : LocalDateTime
    - pickedUpAt : LocalDateTime
    - deliveredAt : LocalDateTime
    - observers : List<DeliveryObserver>
    --
    + assignRider(rider) : void
    + pickUp() : void
    + deliver() : void
    + cancel(reason) : void
    + registerObserver(obs) : void
    + notifyObservers() : void
}

enum DeliveryStatus {
    PENDING
    ASSIGNED
    PICKED_UP
    DELIVERED
    CANCELLED
    FAILED
}

note bottom of DeliveryState #FFCDD2
    **STEP 8 - Delivery lifecycle.**
    "**State Pattern** — each state is a class.
    **Pending**: waiting for rider assignment.
    **Assigned**: rider heading to dark store.
    **PickedUp**: rider has the package.
    **Delivered/Cancelled**: terminal.
    **Failed**: rider couldn't deliver, retry."

    Pending -> Assigned -> PickedUp -> Delivered
    Assigned/PickedUp -> Failed -> Assigned (retry)
    Pending/Assigned -> Cancelled
    **Pattern: State | SRP, OCP**
end note

DeliveryState <|.. PendingState
DeliveryState <|.. AssignedState
DeliveryState <|.. PickedUpState
DeliveryState <|.. DeliveredState
DeliveryState <|.. CancelledState
DeliveryState <|.. FailedState
Delivery --> DeliveryState : delegates >
Delivery --> DeliveryStatus
Delivery --> DeliveryRequest : for >
Delivery --> Rider : assigned to >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 9: OBSERVER — Notifications
' ====================================================================
interface DeliveryObserver <<Observer>> {
    + onDeliveryUpdate(delivery, event) : void
}

class CustomerNotifyObserver {
    + onDeliveryUpdate(delivery, event) : void
}

class DarkStoreObserver {
    + onDeliveryUpdate(delivery, event) : void
}

class ETAUpdateObserver {
    + onDeliveryUpdate(delivery, event) : void
}

class MetricsObserver {
    + onDeliveryUpdate(delivery, event) : void
}

class NotificationService {
    - strategies : List<NotificationStrategy>
    --
    + notify(recipient, message) : void
}

interface NotificationStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + send(recipient, message) : void
}

class PushNotification {
    + send(recipient, message) : void
}

class SMSNotification {
    + send(recipient, message) : void
}

note bottom of DeliveryObserver #B2EBF2
    **STEP 9 - Everyone gets notified.**
    "On every state change, Delivery calls
    notifyObservers(). **Observer Pattern**:"

    "**CustomerObserver**: 'Rider is 2 min away!'
    **DarkStoreObserver**: 'Rider arriving for pickup.'
    **ETAObserver**: recalculates live ETA.
    **MetricsObserver**: logs for analytics
    (avg pickup time, delivery SLA %)."

    "Notification via **Strategy**: Push, SMS."
    **Patterns: Observer + Strategy | OCP, SRP**
end note

DeliveryObserver <|.. CustomerNotifyObserver
DeliveryObserver <|.. DarkStoreObserver
DeliveryObserver <|.. ETAUpdateObserver
DeliveryObserver <|.. MetricsObserver
Delivery --> DeliveryObserver : notifies >
NotificationStrategy <|.. PushNotification
NotificationStrategy <|.. SMSNotification
NotificationService --> NotificationStrategy : delegates >
CustomerNotifyObserver --> NotificationService : uses >
RiderMatchingService --> NotificationService


' ====================================================================
'  MATCH RESULT — Returned to caller
' ====================================================================
class MatchResult {
    - success : boolean
    - delivery : Delivery
    - rider : Rider
    - estimatedPickupMin : double
    - estimatedDeliveryMin : double
    - matchTimeMs : long
    - strategyUsed : String
    - fallbackUsed : boolean
    --
    + isSuccess() : boolean
    + getTotalETAMin() : double
}

note bottom of MatchResult #C8E6C9
    **Final result returned to caller.**
    "MatchResult: success, assigned rider,
    ETA to pickup (2 min), ETA to deliver
    (8 min), total 10 min. Shows which
    strategy was used, whether fallback
    was triggered. Transparent + auditable."
end note

RiderMatchingService --> MatchResult : returns >
MatchResult --> Delivery
MatchResult --> Rider


' ====================================================================
'  WRAP UP
' ====================================================================
note as WRAPUP #FFFDE7
    **WRAP UP:** "Order packed at dark store -> RiderMatchingService gets
    available riders from zone-indexed RiderPool -> MatchingStrategy finds
    candidates (nearest/rated/least-loaded) -> RiderScorer ranks them ->
    AssignmentPolicy assigns (direct/broadcast/batch) -> Delivery created
    in Pending state -> rider assigned, state moves through lifecycle (**State**)
    -> customer, store, ETA tracker all notified (**Observer**).
    5 patterns: **Facade**, **Strategy** (x3: matching, assignment, notification),
    **Composite**, **State**, **Observer**. Handles surge via LoadBalancer."
end note


' ====================================================================
'  LEGEND
' ====================================================================
legend bottom
    |= Step |= What Happens |= Pattern |= SOLID |
    | 1 | Order packed, RiderMatchingService called | Facade | SRP, DIP |
    | 2 | DeliveryRequest: pickup/dropoff location, priority, vehicle type | -- | SRP |
    | 3 | Rider: location, status, vehicle, rating. RiderPool indexes by zone | -- | SRP |
    | 4 | Find candidates: nearest, rating-based, least-loaded, composite | Strategy + Composite | OCP, DIP |
    | 5 | Score riders: weighted distance + rating + load + vehicle fit | -- | SRP |
    | 6 | Assign: auto-assign (peak) vs broadcast (scheduled) vs batch | Strategy | OCP, DIP |
    | 7 | LoadBalancer: detect zone overload, surge, rebalance riders | -- | SRP |
    | 8 | Delivery: Pending -> Assigned -> PickedUp -> Delivered / Failed | State | SRP, OCP |
    | 9 | Customer, dark store, ETA tracker, metrics all notified | Observer + Strategy | OCP, SRP |
    |  |  |  |  |
    | **Match** = Steps 4-6 | **Deliver** = Step 8 | **Notify** = Step 9 | **Scale** = Step 7 |
endlegend

@enduml
